WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.255 --> 00:00:20.955
How many of you are tired of seeing celebrities adopting kids from the African continent?
你们之中有多少人已经对那些从非洲领养小孩的明星而感到厌倦了？

2
00:00:20.979 --> 00:00:22.558
(Laughter)
（笑声）

3
00:00:24.162 --> 00:00:26.516
Well, it's not all that bad.
嗯，那也不全是坏事。

4
00:00:28.393 --> 00:00:29.761
I was adopted.
我就是被其中领养的一员。

5
00:00:31.271 --> 00:00:33.973
I grew up in rural Uganda,
我在乌干达的郊区长大，

6
00:00:35.315 --> 00:00:38.083
lost both my parents when I was very, very young.
在我很小的时候，我的父母就去世了。

7
00:00:39.798 --> 00:00:41.517
And when my parents passed,
在我父母离世之后，

8
00:00:42.287 --> 00:00:48.428
I experienced all the negative effects of poverty,
我经历了所有贫困带来的困难，

9
00:00:49.180 --> 00:00:50.799
from homelessness,
从无家可归，

10
00:00:50.823 --> 00:00:52.592
eating out of trash piles,
到捡食路边的垃圾，

11
00:00:53.359 --> 00:00:54.509
you name it.
所有你能想得到的。

12
00:00:56.423 --> 00:01:02.671
But my life changed when I got accepted into an orphanage.
但自从我被一家孤儿院收养我的生活就发生了巨变。

13
00:01:03.628 --> 00:01:05.975
Through one of those sponsor-an-orphan programs,
通过孤儿院的一个补助项目，

14
00:01:06.744 --> 00:01:10.451
I was sponsored and given an opportunity to acquire an education.
我获得了接受教育的机会，以及相应的资助。

15
00:01:11.783 --> 00:01:13.893
I started off in Uganda.
一开始是在乌干达。

16
00:01:13.917 --> 00:01:17.671
I went through school, and the way this particular program worked,
我去了学校念书，而根据这个项目的运作流程，

17
00:01:17.695 --> 00:01:19.903
you finished high school and after high school,
他们会在你读完高中以后，

18
00:01:19.927 --> 00:01:23.587
you go learn a trade -- to become a carpenter, a mechanic
送你去学一门手艺，比如木匠，或者机修工

19
00:01:23.611 --> 00:01:25.411
or something along those lines.
或者其他的一些专业技术。

20
00:01:26.379 --> 00:01:29.247
My case was a little different.
而我的情况却有所不同。

21
00:01:30.128 --> 00:01:34.221
The sponsor family that was sending these 25 dollars a month
每个月我会在孤儿院收到25美元补助。

22
00:01:34.245 --> 00:01:36.657
to this orphanage to sponsor me,
这钱来自资助我的家庭，

23
00:01:36.681 --> 00:01:38.533
which -- I had never met them --
我从未见过他们

24
00:01:39.522 --> 00:01:41.357
said, "Well ...
他们说，

25
00:01:42.633 --> 00:01:45.239
we would like to send you to college instead."
“我们希望资助你去上大学”

26
00:01:46.358 --> 00:01:47.586
Oh -- it gets better.
哦，那再好不过了。

27
00:01:47.610 --> 00:01:48.653
(Laughter)
（笑声）

28
00:01:48.677 --> 00:01:51.513
And they said, "If you get the paperwork,
他们还说：“如果你能通过申请

29
00:01:51.537 --> 00:01:54.440
we'll send you to school in America instead."
我们会把你送到美国的大学读书。“

30
00:01:56.676 --> 00:01:58.263
So with their help,
所以，在他们的帮助下，

31
00:01:59.107 --> 00:02:02.403
I went to the embassy and applied for the visa.
我去大使馆申请了签证。

32
00:02:03.036 --> 00:02:04.425
I got the visa.
并且通过了签证。

33
00:02:04.449 --> 00:02:08.480
I remember this day like it was yesterday.
那一天对我来说就像昨天一样。

34
00:02:08.874 --> 00:02:12.238
I walked out of the embassy with this piece of paper in my hand,
我拿着手里的文件走出大使馆，

35
00:02:12.262 --> 00:02:13.977
a hop in my step,
一路蹦跳，

36
00:02:14.001 --> 00:02:15.702
smile on my face,
难掩笑意，

37
00:02:15.726 --> 00:02:19.113
knowing that my life is about to change.
我明白我的生活将不复从前。

38
00:02:20.695 --> 00:02:22.285
I went home that night,
那天晚上我回到家里，

39
00:02:22.988 --> 00:02:24.802
and I slept with my passport,
抱着我的护照睡着了，

40
00:02:24.826 --> 00:02:27.133
because I was afraid that someone might steal it.
因为我担心有人会把它偷走。

41
00:02:27.157 --> 00:02:29.012
(Laughter)
（笑声）

42
00:02:29.036 --> 00:02:30.456
I couldn't fall asleep.
而我辗转反侧。

43
00:02:31.266 --> 00:02:32.584
I kept feeling it.
那念头依然挥之不去。

44
00:02:33.716 --> 00:02:35.545
I had a good idea for security.
我突然想到了一个万全的主意。

45
00:02:36.144 --> 00:02:38.713
I was like, "OK, I'm going to put it in a plastic bag,
我说：”好吧，我可以把它放进一个塑料袋里

46
00:02:38.737 --> 00:02:42.244
and take it outside and dig a hole, and put it in there."
然后在外面地上挖一个洞，把袋子放进去。”

47
00:02:43.526 --> 00:02:45.471
I did that, went back in the house.
我真的做了，然后又回到屋子里。

48
00:02:45.495 --> 00:02:48.448
I could not fall asleep. I was like, "Maybe someone saw me."
但我依然无眠，我想，“也许有人看到我了。”

49
00:02:48.472 --> 00:02:49.623
I went back --
我又回去了

50
00:02:49.647 --> 00:02:50.657
(Laughter)
（笑声）

51
00:02:50.681 --> 00:02:53.455
I pulled it out, and I put it with me the entire night --
我把袋子拿出来，然后抓着它度过了一宿

52
00:02:53.479 --> 00:02:56.437
all to say that it was an anxiety-filled night.
我只想说那真是焦虑的一晚。

53
00:02:56.461 --> 00:02:57.611
(Laughter)
（笑声）

54
00:02:58.023 --> 00:03:02.074
Going to the US was, just like another speaker said,
来到美国的感受，和其他初来乍到的人一样

55
00:03:02.098 --> 00:03:04.452
was my first time to see a plane,
那是我第一次坐飞机，

56
00:03:04.476 --> 00:03:07.837
be on one, let alone sit on it to fly to another country.
坐在座位上，飞向另一个国家。

57
00:03:08.992 --> 00:03:11.501
December 15, 2006.
2006年12月15日

58
00:03:11.881 --> 00:03:13.771
7:08pm.
晚上7点08分

59
00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:17.369
I sat in seat 7A.
我坐在7A座位上。

60
00:03:17.829 --> 00:03:19.172
Fly Emirates.
乘坐阿联酋航班。

61
00:03:21.247 --> 00:03:24.925
One of the most gorgeous, beautiful women I've ever seen walked up,
一个我有生以来见过的最美的女人朝我走来，

62
00:03:26.066 --> 00:03:28.872
red little hat with a white veil.
她戴着红色的帽子和白色的口罩。

63
00:03:29.612 --> 00:03:32.545
I'm looking terrified, I have no idea what I'm doing.
我真的吓坏了，我简直手足无措。

64
00:03:33.211 --> 00:03:35.437
She hands me this warm towel --
她递给我一张温热的纸巾

65
00:03:35.461 --> 00:03:37.542
warm, steamy, snow white.
温暖，湿润，白净如雪。

66
00:03:39.506 --> 00:03:41.820
I'm looking at this warm towel;
我盯着这张温暖的纸巾；

67
00:03:41.844 --> 00:03:45.238
I don't know what to do with my life, let alone with this damn towel --
我都不知道我该拿我的生活怎么办，更别说这张纸巾了

68
00:03:45.262 --> 00:03:47.139
(Laughter)
（笑声）

69
00:03:47.163 --> 00:03:49.981
(Applause)
（掌声）

70
00:03:51.532 --> 00:03:52.871
I did one of the --
我做了一件 --

71
00:03:52.895 --> 00:03:55.385
you know, anything anyone could do in that situation:
你懂的，任何人都会做的事：

72
00:03:55.863 --> 00:03:58.560
look around, see what everyone else is doing.
我环顾四周，看其他人的举动。

73
00:03:58.584 --> 00:03:59.768
I did the same.
然后我也跟着他们做。

74
00:04:00.369 --> 00:04:05.406
Mind you, I drove about seven hours from my village to the airport that day.
顺便一提，从村子到机场，那一天我开了7个小时的车。

75
00:04:06.344 --> 00:04:08.394
So I grab this warm towel,
所以我拿起那张温暖的纸，

76
00:04:08.418 --> 00:04:11.563
wipe my face just like everyone else is doing,
效仿着别人擦拭了自己的脸，

77
00:04:11.587 --> 00:04:13.033
I look at it --
我看了看纸巾 --

78
00:04:13.057 --> 00:04:14.222
damn.
该死。

79
00:04:14.246 --> 00:04:15.738
(Laughter)
（笑声）

80
00:04:16.803 --> 00:04:18.641
It was all dirt brown.
已经变成屎黄色了。

81
00:04:18.665 --> 00:04:19.815
(Laughter)
（笑声）

82
00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:26.015
I remember being so embarrassed that when she came by to pick it up,
我记得我是那么的尴尬，以至于当她来回收纸巾的时候，

83
00:04:26.039 --> 00:04:27.266
I didn't give mine.
我没好意思给她。

84
00:04:27.290 --> 00:04:28.407
(Laughter)
(笑声)

85
00:04:28.431 --> 00:04:29.599
I still have it.
我现在都还带着它。

86
00:04:29.623 --> 00:04:31.294
(Laughter)
（笑声）

87
00:04:31.318 --> 00:04:33.288
(Applause)
（掌声）

88
00:04:34.770 --> 00:04:37.708
Going to America opened doors for me
美国向我敞开了大门

89
00:04:37.732 --> 00:04:40.622
to live up to my full God-given potential.
让我能够发挥自己最大的潜力。

90
00:04:41.682 --> 00:04:43.211
I remember when I arrived,
我记得我刚到的时候，

91
00:04:43.235 --> 00:04:45.200
the sponsor family embraced me,
我的资助家庭迎接了我，

92
00:04:45.224 --> 00:04:48.553
and they literally had to teach me everything from scratch:
然后他们就把一切从头开始教给我：

93
00:04:48.577 --> 00:04:51.325
this is a microwave, that's a refrigerator --
这是一个微波炉，那是一个冰箱--

94
00:04:51.349 --> 00:04:54.058
things I'd never seen before.
那些都是我以前闻所未闻的东西。

95
00:04:54.082 --> 00:04:59.217
And it was also the first time I got immersed into a new and different culture.
那也是我第一次被放置在全新的文化环境当中。

96
00:04:59.979 --> 00:05:05.715
These strangers showed me true love.
这些陌生人向我展示了真正的关爱。

97
00:05:06.900 --> 00:05:10.602
These strangers showed me that I mattered,
这些陌生人让我明白，我很重要

98
00:05:11.858 --> 00:05:14.245
that my dreams mattered.
我的梦想很重要。

99
00:05:21.985 --> 00:05:26.264
(Applause)
（掌声）

100
00:05:28.661 --> 00:05:29.811
Thank you.
谢谢。

101
00:05:32.528 --> 00:05:35.775
These individuals had two of their own biological children.
他们有两个亲生孩子。

102
00:05:36.299 --> 00:05:39.067
And when I came in, I had needs.
当我走进他们家庭的时候，我急需帮助。

103
00:05:39.511 --> 00:05:41.584
They had to teach me English,
他们要教我英文，

104
00:05:41.608 --> 00:05:44.392
teach me literally everything,
教我几乎所有的事情，

105
00:05:44.416 --> 00:05:47.143
which resulted in them spending a lot of time with me.
这导致他们要在我的身上 花费很多的精力。

106
00:05:47.546 --> 00:05:52.980
And that created a little bit of jealousy with their children.
而这致使他们的亲生孩子对我产生了一丝妒忌。

107
00:05:54.975 --> 00:05:59.484
So, if you're a parent in this room,
所以，如果你们有人是家长，

108
00:05:59.508 --> 00:06:02.517
and you have those teenager children
而你又有这样一群青少年小孩

109
00:06:02.541 --> 00:06:06.895
who don't want anything to do with your love and affection --
他们对你们的爱和关心置若罔闻

110
00:06:06.919 --> 00:06:08.746
in fact, they find it repulsive --
事实上，还对你们很冷淡

111
00:06:09.521 --> 00:06:11.074
I got a solution:
我有一个办法：

112
00:06:11.098 --> 00:06:12.470
adopt a child.
领养一个孩子。

113
00:06:12.494 --> 00:06:13.506
(Laughter)
（笑声）

114
00:06:13.530 --> 00:06:14.770
It will solve the problem.
问题就会迎刃而解。

115
00:06:14.794 --> 00:06:16.925
(Applause)
（掌声）

116
00:06:19.094 --> 00:06:24.218
I went on to acquire two engineering degrees from one of the best institutions in the world.
在一所世界一流学府中我习得了两个工程师学位。

117
00:06:24.993 --> 00:06:26.258
I've got to tell you:
我必须要说：

118
00:06:26.282 --> 00:06:28.099
talent is universal,
天赋人人都有，

119
00:06:28.123 --> 00:06:30.285
but opportunities are not.
但机会一缘难求。

120
00:06:31.558 --> 00:06:32.979
And I credit this
我想要赞美

121
00:06:34.116 --> 00:06:37.664
to the individuals who embrace multiculturalism,
那些拥抱多元文化的人，

122
00:06:38.567 --> 00:06:42.355
love, empathy and compassion for others.
那些关爱，理解并且同情他人的人。

123
00:06:44.392 --> 00:06:47.394
We live in a world filled with hate:
我们生活在一个充满憎恨的世界上：

124
00:06:47.418 --> 00:06:49.016
building walls,
高筑围墙，

125
00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:50.334
Brexit,
英国脱欧，

126
00:06:50.358 --> 00:06:53.837
xenophobia here on the African continent.
非洲大陆的仇外心理。

127
00:06:55.146 --> 00:07:01.196
Multiculturalism can be an answer to many of these worst human qualities.
而这些人类最负面的东西都可以被多元文化海涵。

128
00:07:03.128 --> 00:07:05.916
Today, I challenge you
今天，我挑战你们在座的观众们

129
00:07:05.940 --> 00:07:09.854
to help a young child experience multiculturalism.
去帮助一个年轻的孩子感受多元文化的魅力。

130
00:07:10.985 --> 00:07:15.068
I guarantee you that will enrich their life,
我保证那会充实他的生活，

131
00:07:15.092 --> 00:07:16.735
and in turn,
作为回报，

132
00:07:16.759 --> 00:07:18.137
it will enrich yours.
你们的生活也会得到升华。

133
00:07:19.339 --> 00:07:21.003
And as a bonus,
而作为奖励，

134
00:07:21.027 --> 00:07:23.040
one of them may even give a TED Talk.
他们其中之一也许还会在TED演讲。

135
00:07:23.064 --> 00:07:24.547
(Laughter)
（笑声）

136
00:07:25.089 --> 00:07:27.454
(Applause)
（掌声）

137
00:07:30.038 --> 00:07:34.960
We may not be able to solve the bigotry and the racism of this world today,
我们也许无力解决当今社会的种族歧视与偏见，

138
00:07:34.984 --> 00:07:38.688
but certainly we can raise children
但我们完全可以引导我们的孩子

139
00:07:39.592 --> 00:07:43.090
to create a positive, inclusive, connected world
去创建一个积极的，包容的，紧密相连的世界。

140
00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:45.207
full of empathy,
那里将充满理解，

141
00:07:46.110 --> 00:07:47.388
love
关爱，

142
00:07:47.412 --> 00:07:48.702
and compassion.
同情。

143
00:07:49.181 --> 00:07:50.353
Love wins.
真爱无敌。

144
00:07:50.377 --> 00:07:51.527
Thank you.
谢谢。

145
00:07:51.551 --> 00:07:54.590
(Applause)
（掌声）